Title: WMS Analyst
Description:
The WMS Analyst for our Warehouse Management System (WMS) will primarily serve Ulta’s Distribution Center by providing timely and accurate data, process and system analysis for improving warehousing and transportation efficiencies. The Analyst is expected to be part of a rotational 24/7 on-call group that will support the operation at all hours. The role has multiple responsibilities that are carried out without direct supervision from management, yet hold significant operational, efficiency, and financial implications.Top Reasons to Work with UsGreat pay, excellent benefits and career growth!!What You Will Be Doing• Support the Distribution Center’s 24/7 operation in regards to the Manhattan WMOS, WCS, and Lightning Pick systems • Troubleshooting complex systems issues, creating and maintaining SQL-based Business Intelligence Reporting, active partnership with appropriate departments from ULTA HQ and various vendors. • This position is the first point of contact in the systems issue escalation process and is required to make informed, educated decisions apart from the WMS Manager. • Maintain inventory integrity between Manhattan WMOS and SAP. • This responsibility has both operational and financial implications to ULTA and is done under minimal or no supervision from management. • This is a highly impactful responsibility which requires daily interaction including reviewing & maintaining inventory sync & error handling reports, same day research and resolution of discrepancies, participating and leading daily inventory sync calls & collaborating with the HQ partners, Finance team and DC Ops teams to provide training and guidance for sync discrepancy prevention • Maintain slotting requirements with input from the operation. • Keep management, other team members and other departmental employees aware of obstacles and status changes in a timely manner. Use proper judgment to determine when such communication is necessary. • Consider the need for other team members to support their areas of responsibility and openly shares an understanding of these areas. • Ensure his/her areas of expertise are covered when absent. • Analyze production issues as necessary to determine the cause of the issue and determine the necessary course of action for resolution. • Responsible for testing the solution and verifying that the production issue has indeed been resolved following implementation. • Consider technical and performance consequences when creating design deliverables. • Use technical skills in the appropriate toolset to analyze data and develop necessary "work arounds." Deliverables in this area are typically used to support the design and support process, not to be rolled out for productive use by business users. • Create and deliver user documentation as necessary to ensure proper use of changed and newly implemented efforts.What You Need for this PositionJOB REQUIREMENTS Minimum: Bachelor’s degree in related field (Computer Science, Business, IT, Analytics, Engineering), or equivalent related work experience Executive level communication skills possessing the ability to directly and clearly communicate complex ideas to a team Ability to multi-task and thrive under pressure Experience developing training programs and coaching both leaders and frontline employees 1-3 years of Manhattan experience OR 5+ years of Oracle/DBA/Analytics experience Experience writing SQL Scripting or ad-hoc reporting experience Experience with live systems, such as SAP Proficiency in Microsoft Access and Excel High learning agility. Position will often require learning new areas of business, new software and new technology. Strong experience with data analysis/design and systems analysis/design. Experience with warehouse management systems. Experience with transportation management systems. Experience with labor management systems. MS Excel, Word, Access SPECIAL POSITION REQUIREMENTS Preferred: 3+ years of leadership experience, preferably in a distribution environment 3+ years of WMS experience 1+ years of SOX compliance experience 1+ yearsWhat's In It for YouGreat pay, excellent benefits and career growth!!So, if you are a WMS Analyst, please apply today!

Title: Security Analyst
Description:
If you are a Security Analyst with experience, please read on!Based in beautiful San Antonio, TX, we are a an innovative managed security service provider with a mission to protect customer data and make technology available, productive, and secure with the strongest talent in the industry. We are looking for a hardworking Security Analyst who has strong SIEM experience in an information security role to add to our growing team. If this sounds like something you'd be interested in, we'd love to tell you more about this opportunity!What You Will Be DoingThe Security Analyst is responsible for reviewing system log events and data packets to determine whether activity is normal or malicious. The Security Analyst will ensure that aspects of the customers’ environments are identified and understood to enable accurate actionable reporting for other tiers. Analysts will also participate in developing processes, procedures, training, etc. for new technologies. Strong knowledge of incident response principles and phases. Other duties may include:-Performing systems and network analysis of intrusions to customers’ network infrastructure, applications, operating systems, firewalls, proxy devices, malware detection and more and work as part of the team conducting preliminary incident response, event analysis and threat intelligence.-Conduct initial and ongoing tuning of customers’ environments from on-boarding to day 2.-Participate in solutions development for new products as they are introduced to the organization.-Handling escalations from Security Specialists and Associate Analysts.-Reviewing security events that are detrimental to the overall security posture; analyze and detect sophisticated and nuanced attacks, discern false positives.-Providing both strategic analysis and near real-time auditing, investigating, reporting, and remediation, coordinating and tracking of security-related activities for customers.-Conducting vulnerability testing.What You Need for this Position-3+ experience in an information security role-Knowledge of web application security and in vulnerability management required-SIEM experience is a MUST: Interpret log data, read log messages, packet inspection-IPS/IDS: Writing signatures or investigating events-Network security attacks, vectors and network protocols including TCP, UDP, ICMP, SNMP, HTTP, and FTP-Experience with network troubleshooting of workstations, server, switches, and routers-Operating systems knowledge and systems administration skills for various versions of UNIX, LINUX, and Windows and ability to read and understand Windows logs-Strong knowledge of the various security solutions such as AV, IPS, IDS, SIEM, firewalls and proxies-Incident Handling procedures-Information security in multi-platform environmentProfessional certifications such as CompTIA+, Network+, SANS/GIAC are a plusWhat's In It for You-Top pay!-Comprehensive benefits-401K-PTO/Sick leave-Work with cutting edge technology-Huge growth potential!So, if you are a Security Analyst with experience, please apply today!

Title: IT Audit/Compliance Analyst
Description:
If you are an IT Audit/Compliance Analyst, please read on!We are a global organization looking for an IT Audit/Compliance Analyst to join our team.  This is a new position within a newly formed group of internal IT auditing that sits inside of our technology department.  The goal of this role and the team is to ensure that all technology whether applications, infrastructure and operations are compliant to the company's internal processes and controls and external compliance that is required.  You will create policies and procedures around IT compliance and educate the department to ensure adherence to them.  This role will perform IT audits and control reviews for anything within the technology function responsibility. Title: Senior Marketing Analyst
Description:
If you are a Senior Marketing Analyst with experience, please read on!What You Will Be DoingSUMMARY: The Marketing Manager / Marketing Analyst will be responsible for managing direct marketing campaigns (catalog and email) from inception to completion including providing input on strategy and analyzing results against goals to improve campaign effectiveness. Works with the e-Commerce Director, Creative Director, Web Merchant and other marketing members to generate the profitable acquisition of new customers and retention and reactivation of existing customers. As the key owner of the customer file, the position is responsible for optimizing customer segments through direct marketing channels, analyzing, reporting, forecasting and budgeting the direct marketing activities.Essential Job Responsibilities: •Manages the direct marketing and contact plan (circulation / segment plan) to optimize return-on-investment for customer acquisition, retention and reactivation. •Identifies, develops and delivers the execution of high-impact direct marketing campaigns primarily through email and DM catalogs and mail pieces.•Manages all day-to-day aspects of the Direct Marketing program including list selection, working with the creative and copy teams, budgeting, reporting, optimization and vendor management.•Leverages the newly launched Marketing Database (MDB) and analytics tools (Campaign Runner, Tableau), and supports email and catalog marketing as the lead resource on list selection and segmentation. •As a power-user of the MDB, provides ad-hoc analysis and reporting. Gains a deep understanding of all customer segments through research and analysis to influence direct mail and email channel strategy.•Manages all triggered and batch & blast email campaigns.•Responsible for planning and developing the marketing calendar and communications.•Acts as the primary owner of key reporting and analysis, response reporting, ROI estimates and analysis, customer database KPI’s including monthly reports, file size (customer retention / loyalty, acquisition, re-activation, etc.), marketing goal tracking, and campaign performance. •Forecasts program performance and partners closely with the marketing leadership team to develop direct marketing program budgets.•Manages test design (including hold-out and A/B split, and multi-variate tests with customer segments, creative and messaging) as well as post-mortem reporting.•Works with the Senior Vice President of Marketing and others to set strategic targets and goals for direct mail programs.•Works with the creative team and copywriter, sales manager, and other marketing and merchandising members to ensure product and channel messaging is effective and compelling.•Completes position-specific training, and engages in continuous development.Qualifications: •Bachelor’s degree in Business, Marketing, or relevant coursework required•5+ years of utilizing both direct marketing databases and executing high-impact, direct-response marketing campaigns (catalog and ecommerce environments preferred)•5+ years of reporting and admin management•Strong analytical skills and eager to use quantitative analysis of results to improve the program•Exceptionally organized, “buttoned up” and detail oriented; has a sense of ownership with a commitment to continual improvement•Excellent written and verbal communication skills; strong creative insight and brand experience; must be comfortable communicating across diverse audiences•Experience managing marketing automation platforms and interfacing with marketing service providers•Ability to work collaboratively with colleagues and staff to create a results-driven, team-oriented environment•Power user of Excel preferred. Strong computer skills, working knowledge of MS Office (Word, Outlook, etc.)•Experience with EMS (email marketing systems), data flows, and marketing automation tools (such as Campaign Runner and Tableau) a plusWhat You Need for this PositionAt Least 3 Years of experience and knowledge of:- Excel- Tableau- Pivot Tables- SQL- Advanced statistics & analytics and visualizationSo, if you are a Senior Marketing Analyst with experience, please apply today!
                

                    Applicants must be authorized to work in the U.S.
Skills:
Preferred Skills
                
                    
                            
                                
                                    
                                    Excel

Title: Manufacturing Quality Analyst
Description:
If you are a Manufacturing Quality Analyst or Technician with strong QA experience, please read on!As one of the most experienced and integrated aluminum foundries in Massachusetts, we boast a high production facility with in-house production processes from core making and assembly, heat treating, CNC machining, product final assembly and supply chain management. We specialize in complex, highly-cored casting for numerous applications in sizes ranging from a few ounces to 100+ pounds, all produced on state-of-the-art equipment.We are seeking a Quality Analyst or Technician with experience to join our team of casting experts!Top Reasons to Work with Us- Well Established Leader for Over 50+ Years- Great Compensation (50k-65k)- Leading State of the Art Technologies- Great Team and Leadership- Vacation/PTO- Generous Benefits PackageWhat You Will Be Doing•Determine and/or obtain part-specific PMM requirements for new and existing parts•Enters part-specific requirements into PMM Tracker and saves supporting documentation to network directory•Inspects parts using various inspection equipment and basic tools (calipers, gauges, fixtures, etc.) •Accept or reject part per the required specification•Enters inspection results into Tracker and saves to network directory•Completes all necessary paperwork accurately, efficiently, and in a timely manner•Creates and affixes labels, tags, and/or other rejection markers to inspected product dispositioned as nonconforming or potentially nonconforming and reports quality issues to appropriate personnel•Ensures that all required inspections are performed, passed, and recorded in PMM Tracker before releasing product to Final Inspection operation•Cross trains in metal and sand testing, simple instructions, short correspondence•Computer:  Good working knowledge of Windows, Excel, Word, Outlook, Geomagic Control X, Quality Analyst•Soft Skills:  Willing and able to clearly and effectively communicate in English language (both written and verbal) in one-on-one, small group situations, and with all levels of the organization.  •Math:  Add, subtract, divide in all units of measure, using whole numbers, common fractions, and decimals; trigonometry; statistical process control•GD&T:  Understand and interpret prints and specifications•Contact measurement skills:  Use of functional gauges, height gauges, verniers, etc.- Machining Background preferredSo, if you are a Quality Technician or Quality Analyst with experience, please apply today!

Benefits & Comp:• Health & MedicalAll Full time employees can elect coverage for Medical/Prescription coverage, Dental, Vision and Life Insurance.• Retirement- 401KWe are proud that we offer an opportunity for employees to prepare for retirement with a 401K company-sponsored Saving and Investment Program (company matches 50% up to 6% of employee contributions).• EAP programWe offer an Employee Assistance Program that is available 24/7 to all employees, all their household members and immediate family members.• Vacation and HolidaysWe celebrate 11 U.S. Holidays each year. Title: Senior Application Security Analyst/Developer
Description:
If you are a Senior Application Security Analyst with experience, please read on! We are looking for a Developer who has a great interest in Security, and can liaison between the development team and the application security team.What You Will Be DoingGeneral Qualifications:-The senior application security analyst will work with the various development teams to implement application security practices that meet our defined policies and standards for information security.-The senior application security analyst must analyze information security systems/applications; make recommendations and develop security measures to protect information against unauthorized modification or loss.-The senior application security analyst will serve as subject matter expert for best practices and security controlsEfforts will include:-Serving as a subject matter expert for security in application projects-Driving secure application development practices and a secure development mentality-Managing the application vulnerability assessment process and tools (SAST and DAST) focused on web, client-server, and mobile applications-Identifying, communicating, and driving the resolution of vulnerabilities-Developing and updating security patterns aligned with security requirements-Identifying application security requirements for projects-Providing reports to development management and business management on the status of vulnerability remediation for their applications-Performing functional requirement reviews and technical design reviews-Coordinating and collaborating with server infrastructure engineering, network infrastructure engineering, business application development, and database administration functions to ensure confidentiality, integrity, and availability of corporate infrastructure meets business demands-Performing other security-related projects that may be assigned according to skillsWhat You Need for this PositionTechnical Experience & Qualifications:-Bachelor’s degree or greater in a technical or business discipline-4-6 years or more of experience, primarily in application development, information security, or a related field, preferably in the financial sector and/or supporting IT Risk or Information Security initiatives-Experience and technical proficiency in major object-oriented programming languages, web front-end languages, frameworks, and libraries (Java, .Net, C++, JavaScript, JSON, SCALA, Groovy, Spring, Log4x, etc.)-Experience and technical proficiency with modern application packaging, deployment, containerizing, bug tracking tools and other supporting tools (Jenkins, Maven, Docker, Kubernetes Jira, Rally, etc.)-Experience and technical proficiency with modern source code management and software repository systems (Git/GitHub, Perforce, Subversion, Team Foundation Server, etc.)-Experience and technical proficiency with developing applications specifically for AWS and Azure Cloud hosting environments-Experience with Static Application Security Testing (SAST), Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST) tools, and enterprise architecture tools-Deep understanding of OWASP Top 10 and SANS Top 25 vulnerabilities-Strong experience with data visualization concepts and tools-Ability to analyze data using Excel including use of complex Excel macros / scripts for reporting purposes; some development experience is preferable-Experience with Veracode (or other SAST/DAST tools), Jira, ServiceNow, and Splunk is preferable-CISSP, GIAC, CISA, CISM, TOGAF certifications preferable-Ability to work individually and as part of a team-Strong written and oral communication skills-Strong presentation skills; ability to adjust message and filter details based on audience (e.g. technical, business, management)So, if you are a Senior Application Security Analyst with experience, please apply today!
                

                    Applicants must be authorized to work in the U.S.
Skills:

                                    SAST

Title: Fuel Pricing & Logistics Analyst
Description:
We are actively recruiting for a Logistics / Pricing Analyst Assistant!  Perhaps you are a recent college graduate with strong analytical skills in logistics and pricing.  Or perhaps no degree but several years of hands on experience allowing for you to hit the ground running.  Core skills include proficiency in Excel as well as the knack for analyzing data to develop and execute pricing strategy.    We are very excited to connect with you.  Please take a moment and make sure we have the most recent copy of your resume as well as answer the skills and questions self assessment.  We will reach out to you shortly!Top Reasons to Work with UsAs a Logistics/Pricing Analyst Assistant, you will become a crucial part of our daily operation and monthly/annual success backing up the Logistics/Pricing Manager. Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
This is a very unique Data Science opportunity!   In this role your time would be split as follows:  2 quarters - teaching at our data science bootcamp in SF, 1 quarter - working on business projects, 1 quarter - you'd get paid to work on data science passion projects of your choice (write a book, work on research, take a consulting assignment - your choice)!  The latter 2 quarters are REMOTE work.We are a highly successful data science boot-camp with locations in NYC, Chicago, Seattle and San Francisco and we're looking for dynamic Data Scientists with a passion for teaching.Top Reasons to Work with Us- Work remote 2 quarters of each year (with some travel) & get paid to work on passion projects of your choice for 1 quarter!- We are a startup company owned by a global giant so you get the best of both worlds - that startup vibe but with security.- Competitive annual salary and full benefits.What You Will Be DoingSENIOR DATA SCIENTISTWe are looking for Data Scientists to be part of the our Data Science Instructional Team.  We seek individuals who love and excel at analyzing and visualizing data to solve important problems, are passionate about teaching others to be premier data scientists, and are fun to be around and work with.  An ideal candidate should be quick to learn and adapt, care about design of simple, powerful, beautiful interfaces and visuals, love writing code, thrive in creative team efforts, and also have interests and passions beyond data science.ResponsibilitiesOur Senior Data Scientists provide incredible and inspiring Data Science instruction; support the design and teaching of new products and courses and infuse their expertise into our business operations; and continually sharpen their skills through consulting and passion project explorations. We call this approach our 2-1-1 Instructor Model. Teaching the Data Science Bootcamp (2 quarters of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend half the year co-teaching two 12-week bootcamps (20-24 students). On any given day, the amount of lecture time is 1-2 hours, and the remainder of the day is spent directly engaging with and coaching individually the students.•Leading course discussions•Providing personalized support to students•Improving the quality of our curriculum •Offering career guidance and interview supportDeveloping and Teaching New Courses and Supporting Business Operations (1 quarter of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend about one-quarter of the year helping to create and teach new course offerings, as well as infusing our functional areas – admissions, marketing, careers, instructor recruitment  – with their domain expertise.•Creating new courses and/or enhancing existing courses•Providing data science training to corporations•Interviewing and providing feedback on applicants•Speaking at events and conferences•Writing articles and blogs•Assisting with instructor recruitmentSharpening Skills and Pursuing Data Science Passion Projects (1 quarter of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend about one-quarter of the year focused entirely on enhancing their skill set and building their data science knowledge in whatever way they choose.  These three months are intended to be self-driven.  Some ideas include:•Consulting on pro bono data science projects (e.g., with DataKind)•Providing in-house data science project expertise to specific companies•Authoring a book related to data science•Enrolling in data science classes•Working on open source passion projectsWhat You Need for this PositionMust haves:Machine Learning AlgorithmsSolid Python experience 2+ years INDUSTRY experience of data science A passion for teachingPreferred (NOT essential):Ideally Masters or PhD in quantitative fieldPrior teaching experienceWhat's In It for YouPerks of the Role•Part of a team that is transforming education•Three paid months per year to sharpen skills and pursue passion projects•Competitive compensation package•Opportunity to network and develop, both among our internal Data Science speaker community, as well as through our parent company which is a global organization•Opportunity to work in different geographic locations if desiredSo, if you are a Data Scientist who wants to teach, get involved in the business AND get paid to spend 3 months a year working on a data science project of your choice, please apply today!

Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
This is a very unique Data Science opportunity!   In this role your time would be split as follows:  2 quarters - teaching at our data science bootcamp in SF, 1 quarter - working on business projects, 1 quarter - you'd get paid to work on data science passion projects of your choice (write a book, work on research, take a consulting assignment - your choice)!  The latter 2 quarters are REMOTE work.We are a highly successful data science boot-camp with locations in NYC, Chicago, Seattle and San Francisco and we're looking for dynamic Data Scientists with a passion for teaching.Top Reasons to Work with Us- Work remote 2 quarters of each year (with some travel) & get paid to work on passion projects of your choice for 1 quarter!- We are a startup company owned by a global giant so you get the best of both worlds - that startup vibe but with security.- Competitive annual salary and full benefits.What You Will Be DoingSENIOR DATA SCIENTISTWe are looking for Data Scientists to be part of the our Data Science Instructional Team.  We seek individuals who love and excel at analyzing and visualizing data to solve important problems, are passionate about teaching others to be premier data scientists, and are fun to be around and work with.  An ideal candidate should be quick to learn and adapt, care about design of simple, powerful, beautiful interfaces and visuals, love writing code, thrive in creative team efforts, and also have interests and passions beyond data science.ResponsibilitiesOur Senior Data Scientists provide incredible and inspiring Data Science instruction; support the design and teaching of new products and courses and infuse their expertise into our business operations; and continually sharpen their skills through consulting and passion project explorations. We call this approach our 2-1-1 Instructor Model. Teaching the Data Science Bootcamp (2 quarters of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend half the year co-teaching two 12-week bootcamps (20-24 students). On any given day, the amount of lecture time is 1-2 hours, and the remainder of the day is spent directly engaging with and coaching individually the students.•Leading course discussions•Providing personalized support to students•Improving the quality of our curriculum •Offering career guidance and interview supportDeveloping and Teaching New Courses and Supporting Business Operations (1 quarter of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend about one-quarter of the year helping to create and teach new course offerings, as well as infusing our functional areas – admissions, marketing, careers, instructor recruitment  – with their domain expertise.•Creating new courses and/or enhancing existing courses•Providing data science training to corporations•Interviewing and providing feedback on applicants•Speaking at events and conferences•Writing articles and blogs•Assisting with instructor recruitmentSharpening Skills and Pursuing Data Science Passion Projects (1 quarter of the year)Senior Data Scientists spend about one-quarter of the year focused entirely on enhancing their skill set and building their data science knowledge in whatever way they choose.  These three months are intended to be self-driven.  Some ideas include:•Consulting on pro bono data science projects (e.g., with DataKind)•Providing in-house data science project expertise to specific companies•Authoring a book related to data science•Enrolling in data science classes•Working on open source passion projectsWhat You Need for this PositionMust haves:Machine Learning AlgorithmsSolid Python experience 2+ years INDUSTRY experience of data science A passion for teachingPreferred (NOT essential):Ideally Masters or PhD in quantitative fieldPrior teaching experienceWhat's In It for YouPerks of the Role•Part of a team that is transforming education•Three paid months per year to sharpen skills and pursue passion projects•Competitive compensation package•Opportunity to network and develop, both among our internal Data Science speaker community, as well as through our parent company which is a global organization•Opportunity to work in different geographic locations if desiredSo, if you are a Data Scientist who wants to teach, get involved in the business AND get paid to spend 3 months a year working on a data science project of your choice, please apply today!

Description:
We're helping people send over $3 billion around the globe driven by our mission to deliver on our promise to immigrants sending money across the world. We are looking for an exceptional Machine Learning Engineer to unlock the full potential of our data and leverage the power of machine learning to make a difference in the organization. The Data Team is a fast paced environment where you will work on high-impact exciting projects to enhance our customer experience, marketing efficiency, and operational excellence.Top Reasons to Work with UsWe are a group of passionate people working to make international payments easier and more transparent on both the web and mobile devices. We are seeking team members to join us that want to make a difference and change an industry. Based in Santa Monica we are a well established mobile advertising technology company that is currently building new products. Our award-winning software empowers marketing and advertising teams at multi-location businesses like Starbucks, Cricket Wireless, Jamba Juice, and Pizza Hut to influence customers on mobile phones at every point in their customer journey. We help our enterprise clients harness the power of the most effective mobile ad networks - Facebook, Google, Snapchat, Apple, Yelp, Bing and more – to drive consumers to visit their stores, shops and restaurants.We are looking for a data-driven product manager with a business mindset and strong communication skills, who is excited to become an integral part of a rapidly growing, cutting-edge technology company. If you are a Sr. Product Manager with 5+ years of professional experience building SaaS, Ad Tech or Marketing Tech products, please read on!What You Will Be DoingBuild world-class marketing tools that drive measurable client successDefine and drive product strategy with an emphasis on the use of location data for media and analytics use casesDevelop and execute the roadmap for our media and data insights productsCoordinate cross-functional team activities to develop and deliver data focused digital products and toolsDevelop user stories, product requirements and forecasting modelsWork with third-party partners and product management teams to conceptualize, build, test and integrate technologies into the other existing product platformsGather input from key internal and external stakeholders to develop product and feature requirementsThink outside the box and challenge the status quoJuggle multiple projects and shift gears accordingly based on evolving prioritiesWhat You Need for this PositionBS/BA, ideally in Business, Human-Computer Interaction, or Computer Science3+ years of product management experience focusing on SaaS, Ad Tech or Marketing Tech productsA sense of urgencyHighly analytical with the ability to prioritize and make decisions based on user feedback and dataDemonstrated ability to lead product as a business and not just a collection of features and usage dataStrong communication skills with proven success partnering with cross-functional teams and external clientsExperience in agile development practices with proven ability to process rapidly changing circumstances, make decisions, and generate specifications quicklyA deep desire to be part of a dynamic, growing startupA creative problem solver who isn’t afraid to roll up his/her sleeves and “do the work”Prior experience with Facebook, Google or Twitter (and their APIs), marketing tech, ad tech or data/reporting products is a huge plusWhat's In It for YouCompetitive base salary, annual performance bonus, excellent PTO), stock options, challenging work environment and much much more!So, if you are a Sr. Product Manager with 5+ years of experience working on building SaaS, Ad Tech or Marketing Tech products, please apply today!

Title: Sr ETL / Tableau Developer
Description:
We are a fast growing organization that is one of the most trusted companies worldwide.  We focus on the development of robust delivery and distribution tools through the use of technology.  Our significant growth and ability to continuously win new business is largely based on the level of flexibility and customization our technology offers.If you are a Sr ETL / Tableau Developer with experience, please read on!What You Will Be DoingAs Sr. ETL/Tableau Developer on the team, you will be working with BI team to design, develop, implement and document data integration processes, as well as influence the long-term evolution of our analytics capability. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with traditional Data Warehouse concept. The candidate should have excellent communication skills and able to work with product owner to develop and define technical requirements. The candidate should have good knowledge and working experience with Tableau.What You Need for this Position•5+ years experience implementing ETL for Data Warehouse and Business Intelligence Solution•7+ Years experience in RDBMS design, development and performance tuning•Ability to create ETL specifications, unit, and system integration test cases•Build reusable components for a scalable ETL methodology such as error handling, logging and recoverability•Deep familiarity with MS SQL Server 2008 R2 to MS SQL Server 2014 database technologies and ETL best practices with MS SQL Server environment•Ability to read and write effective, modular, dynamic (parameterized) and robust code, establish and follow already established code standards, and ETL framework•Experience using Business Intelligence Development Studio to build SSIS packages•Excellent troubleshooting & optimization skills: interpreting ETL logs, performing data validation, dissecting SSIS code, understanding the benefits and drawbacks of parallelism, experience with change data capture, using expressions, scoping of variables, commonly used transforms, event handlers and logging providers, ability to understand and optimize the surrogate key generation and inconsistent data type handling.•Experience in performance tuning of the SSIS packages,  deploying and administering SSIS packages, proficient in utilizing scripting in SSIS, and replacing ActiveX script tasks in DTS with the script task in SSIS.•Ability to capture and research SSIS issues and bugs, build sample test jobs that recreate a bug, and troubleshoot the ETL until successful issue resolution.•Experience with creating data sources for Tableau•Experience with creating visuals with Tableau •Responsible for unit, string, and system testing and assisting in development of UAT test plans•Experience with NoSQL databases such Mongo DB is a plusWhat's In It for You•Competitive compensation•Comprehensive medical, dental and vision benefits•Supplemental benefit options•Generous Paid Time Off•401(k) Employer ContributionSo, if you are a Sr ETL / Tableau Developer with experience, please apply today!

Description:
